# SEO & AI Discovery Standards

## Overview

These standards ensure all web implementations follow SEO best practices and are optimized for AI discovery engines.

## Required Standards

### 1. Meta Tags (Mandatory for Web Pages)

Every public page MUST have:

```tsx
// Required metadata
export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: 'Descriptive Page Title',        // 50-60 characters
  description: 'Compelling description',  // 150-160 characters
  openGraph: { /* ... */ },               // For social sharing
};
```

**Validation Rules:**
- Title: 50-60 characters, unique per page
- Description: 150-160 characters, unique per page
- Canonical URL: Always specified
- Open Graph: title, description, image, url
- Twitter Card: card type, title, description, image

### 2. Structured Data (Required for Content Pages)

| Page Type | Required Schema |
|-----------|-----------------|
| Homepage | Organization, WebSite |
| Blog Post | Article |
| Product | Product, Offer |
| FAQ | FAQPage |
| How-to | HowTo |
| Event | Event |
| Recipe | Recipe |
| Review | Review |

```tsx
// Example: Article pages MUST include
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "...",
  "datePublished": "...",
  "author": { "@type": "Person", "name": "..." }
}
</script>
```

### 3. Image Optimization (Mandatory)

All images MUST:
- Use `next/image` or equivalent optimized component
- Include descriptive `alt` text
- Specify width and height (prevent CLS)
- Use modern formats (WebP, AVIF)
- Be lazy-loaded (except above-fold LCP images)

```tsx
// Required pattern
<Image
  src="/image.jpg"
  alt="Descriptive alt text"  // Required
  width={800}
  height={600}
  loading="lazy"              // Or priority for LCP
/>
```

### 4. Heading Hierarchy (Strict)

- **One H1 per page** - No exceptions
- **Sequential hierarchy** - H1 → H2 → H3 (no skipping levels)
- **Descriptive headings** - Include keywords naturally

```tsx
// Correct
<h1>Main Page Title</h1>
<h2>Section Title</h2>
<h3>Subsection Title</h3>

// Wrong - skips H2
<h1>Main Title</h1>
<h3>Section</h3>  // ❌ Skipped H2
```

### 5. URL Structure (Enforced)

URLs MUST be:
- Lowercase only
- Hyphen-separated (no underscores)
- Descriptive and readable
- Without query parameters for content pages
- Under 75 characters

```tsx
// Good URLs
/blog/how-to-optimize-react-performance
/products/wireless-headphones

// Bad URLs - REJECTED
/Blog/Article                    // ❌ Mixed case
/products/product_123            // ❌ Underscores
/p?id=123                        // ❌ Query params
```

### 6. Core Web Vitals Targets

| Metric | Good | Needs Improvement | Poor |
|--------|------|-------------------|------|
| **LCP** | ≤2.5s | 2.5s-4s | >4s |
| **INP** | ≤200ms | 200ms-500ms | >500ms |
| **CLS** | ≤0.1 | 0.1-0.25 | >0.25 |

**Required optimizations:**
- Images: Use `next/image` with blur placeholder
- Fonts: Use `next/font` with `display: swap`
- Scripts: Use `next/script` with appropriate strategy
- CSS: Minimize render-blocking stylesheets

### 7. Accessibility for SEO

SEO and accessibility overlap significantly:

- **Alt text**: All images MUST have descriptive alt text
- **Link text**: No "click here" - use descriptive text
- **Color contrast**: Minimum 4.5:1 ratio
- **Form labels**: All inputs MUST have associated labels
- **Language**: `<html lang="...">` MUST be set

### 8. Mobile-First (Required)

- Responsive design is mandatory
- No horizontal scroll on mobile
- Touch targets minimum 44x44 pixels
- Viewport meta tag required

```html
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
```

## AI Discovery Standards

### Content Structure for AI

Content MUST be structured for AI extraction:

1. **Lead with the answer** - First 1-2 sentences should directly answer the main question
2. **Use semantic HTML** - `<article>`, `<section>`, `<aside>`, `<nav>`
3. **Include key facts** - Specific data, numbers, dates
4. **Cite sources** - Link to authoritative references
5. **Show freshness** - Display publish and update dates

### Required Content Elements

For informational pages:
- [ ] Summary/TL;DR in first paragraph
- [ ] Key takeaways section
- [ ] Proper heading structure
- [ ] FAQ section for common questions
- [ ] Sources and references section

## Pre-Commit Checklist

Before committing web pages:

- [ ] Title unique and 50-60 characters
- [ ] Meta description unique and 150-160 characters
- [ ] Canonical URL set
- [ ] Open Graph tags complete
- [ ] Structured data valid (test with Google Rich Results)
- [ ] Images have alt text
- [ ] Only one H1 on page
- [ ] Heading hierarchy correct
- [ ] URL follows naming conventions
- [ ] Mobile responsive verified

